# 02_node_tool_query — cold-path diagnostic, read-only verb.
#
# Diagnostic for cold-vs-warm script execution: is the "first script
# FAILs" behaviour we sometimes observe with 01_node_tool_toggle a
# property of THAT script's verb sequence, or of running ANY script
# for the first time in a fresh process?
#
# This script exercises only the read path:
#   - get  reads a property (no state change)
#   - assert reads a property and compares
#
# No invoke. No state mutation. If this FAILs cold-start and PASSes
# warm, then the cold path isn't per-verb — it's session-wide
# warm-up of the substrate's pump machinery.
#
# If this PASSes cold-start while 01 FAILs cold-start, then the
# cold path is specific to invoke()-bearing verbs (probably the
# signal_clicked cascade on first tool switch).
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Fresh Curvz launch.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run.
#   4. Note: PASS or FAIL?
#   5. Run again.
#   6. Note: PASS this time?
#
# The "label" property reads get_label() on the button. Should
# normally be "" for an icon-only toolbar button. We assert that;
# any non-empty string would also be reportable but the empty
# string is what the Node tool ships with.
#
# s188 m1: addressed as `tb_nod` (was `tool.node` pre-migration).

get tb_nod active
get tb_nod label
assert tb_nod label == ""
